{
  "stem": "5471.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And then they called my husband out to hoist the flag, and they carried him around on their shoulders, and they kissed me from all sides.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Yeah, it was good time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "That must have-- that must have been-- that must have been a wonderful day.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was wonderful, wonderful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, they're small.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my husband promised to bring the Jews back as-- to their own places of where they had lived, and he did that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they ask him for the Nazis [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You could send the Nazis to [INAUDIBLE] an [INAUDIBLE] island.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I don't want anything to do with the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he help bringing Jews back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, our war was ended at the 12th of April, but the rest of Holland was freed by the 5th of May.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the Allied troops asked not to let the Jews go home, because they still needed the roads to pull up to Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the Jews were asked to stay in the camp, and try to work at it was were before, that everyone got their food and their laundry and-- And thereafter, the peoples who were living close by had a chance to go back.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the ones, for instance, from Amsterdam, they didn't have any food whatsoever in Amsterdam themselves.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So there even came planes to drop food in Amsterdam and Rotterdam.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after that, my husband tried to get trucks to bring the people back, and that wasn't easy because there were hardly any trucks in Holland left.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the beginning of the war, the Germans stole everything what they could steal.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then you got that there weren't tires anymore, and there wasn't petrol anymore.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so that wasn't easy either.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
